cancelMigration(address,bool).details: Because this function must also be callable by a permissioned migrator, it has an extra migration hook to the nextFundDeployer for the case where cancelMigration() is called directly (rather than via the nextFundDeployer).

params._bypassFailure: True if a failure in either migration hook should be ignored
params._vaultProxy: The VaultProxy contract for which to cancel the migration request

deployVaultProxy(address,address,address.details: Input validation should be handled by the VaultProxy during deployment

params._owner: The account to set as the VaultProxy's owner
params._vaultAccessor: The account to set as the VaultProxy's permissioned accessor
params._vaultLib: The VaultLib library with which to instantiate the VaultProxy

params._bypassFailure: True if a failure in either migration hook should be ignored
params._vaultProxy: The VaultProxy contract for which to execute the migration request

returns.executableTimestamp_: The timestamp at which the migration request can be executed
returns.nextFundDeployer_: The FundDeployer contract address from which the migration request was made
returns.nextVaultAccessor_: The account that will be the next `accessor` on the VaultProxy
returns.nextVaultLib_: The next VaultLib library contract address to set on the VaultProxy

returns.nominatedOwner_: The account that is nominated to be the owner

returns.owner_: The account that is the owner

returns.secondsRemaining_: The number of seconds remaining on the timelock

returns.hasExecutableRequest_: True if a migration request exists and is executable

returns.hasMigrationRequest_: True if a migration request exists

params._nextFundDeployer: The address of the FundDeployer contract

params._nextTimelock: The number of seconds for the new timelock

userdoc.notice: The top-level contract linking multiple releases. It handles the deployment of new VaultProxy instances, and the regulation of fund migration from a previous release to the current one. It can also be referred to for access-control based on this contract's owner.
